{"questionId":"27702","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle moves in a straight line. Its displacement, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi></math> metres, from a fixed point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math> at&nbsp;time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>, as shown in the following graph.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0f93d8dfeb35b4287bd371d2a42be592699f154c.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the intervals of time when the particle is moving away from the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempting to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> when the particle changes direction&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>433007</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; AND&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25575</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; AND&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33965</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;(may be seen on a graph)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>particle travels away from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math> when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;OR when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>433007</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25575</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33965</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>433</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>26</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>34</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27702","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.7c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the intervals of time when the particle is moving away from the point P.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}